data.chText: （结实的）粗线，细绳；一根粗线（或细绳）
data.enText: strong thick string or thin rope; a piece of this
picture cord (= used for hanging pictures)
a silk bag tied with a gold cord

means: 用索子捆[绑,扎]；堆积(柴薪)

tr: a line made of twisted fibers or threads
example: the bundle was tied with a cord

tr: a cut pile fabric with vertical ribs
a light insulated conductor for household use
a unit of amount of wood cut for burning
bind or tie with a cord

example.ex: The door had been tied shut with a length of nylon cord.
example.tran: 门用一段尼龙绳拴住了。

value.def: Cord is wire covered in rubber or plastic which connects electrical equipment to an electricity supply.

example.ex: We used so many lights that we needed four extension cords.
example.tran: 我们用的灯很多，因此需要4个接线板。

example.ex: He had bare feet, a T-shirt and cords on.
example.tran: 他光着脚，穿着T恤衫和灯芯绒裤子。
